CHAPMAN STUDENT FILM WITH ASNER TO SCREEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Higher Education," a student-written-and-directed four-part dramatic series 
starring Edward Asner, will be screened Wednesday at 8 p.m. at the Academy of 
Television Arts and Sciences' Plaza Theater in North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The work by Chapman University film students will be preceded by a 7 p.m. 
reception, hosted by students and faculty. The events are free and open to the 
public, but reservations are necessary. 
</P>
