<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; GIRL, 14, SURRENDERS IN SLASHING ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Simi Valley summer school student turned herself in Thursday to police, 
admitting she had slashed a 13-year-old girl with a razor knife during a fight, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Mark Layhew said the victim was leaving summer school classes at Hillside 
Junior High School at about 12:30 p.m. Wednesday when a 14-year-old classmate 
walked up and began cursing at her. 
</P>
<P>
 A fight ensued and the 14-year-old attacked the younger girl with a small, 
retractable razor knife such as those used to open boxes, Layhew said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim suffered cuts to her upper and lower chest and arm and abrasions to 
her upper chest, Layhew said. Her brother drove her to Simi Valley Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 She was treated and released, a hospital official said. 
</P>
<P>
 The attacker turned herself in to Simi Valley police late Thursday afternoon. 
She was issued a citation for assault with a deadly weapon and released to her 
mother's custody, Layhew said. The girl's case will be handled by the county 
probation department, he said. MACK REED 
</P>
</TEXT>
