<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: FLAGS AT HALF-STAFF TO HONOR FIRE HEROES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Flags at fire departments throughout Ventura County will fly at half-staff 
until Monday to honor the firefighters who lost their lives in Colorado earlier 
this week while fighting a wildfire, county fire officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 At least 12 "smoke jumpers," specially trained firefighters with the U.S. 
Bureau of Land Management, died Wednesday while battling the 2,200-acre forest 
fire near Glenwood Springs, about 180 miles west of Denver.Two firefighters 
remained missing late Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Flags at Ventura County fire stations will fly at half-staff from 8 a.m. today 
until 8 a.m. Monday, spokeswoman Sandi Wells said. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
