<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; ONE INJURED IN CRASH OF STOLEN TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON GRANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura man suspected of drunken driving crashed a stolen pickup truck at a 
Ventura Freeway interchange Thursday, critically injuring his passenger. 
</P>
<P>
 Several objects -- including a sawed-off shotgun and silverware -- were strewn 
near the crumpled Toyota truck at the junction of the Ojai Freeway.California 
Highway Patrol Officer Staci Morse said some of the objects were apparently 
stolen. 
</P>
<P>
 The wrecked truck also was recently stolen in Tennessee, the home state of the 
injured passenger, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Lopez, 25, was arrested on suspicion of drunken driving and was being 
held in Ventura County Jail. An alcohol blood level was not available late 
Thursday, Morse said. 
</P>
<P>
 The passenger, Anthony Lee Collins, was in intensive care at Ventura County 
Medical Center, a spokeswoman said. He had severe head and spinal injuries, 
internal bleeding and fractured legs. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez attempted to run away from the 7:10 a.m. accident, but a truck driver 
who saw the rollover "grabbed him and walked him back," Morse said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morse said Collins will be arrested on suspicion of possession of a stolen 
vehicle if he recovers. JASON GRANT 
</P>
</TEXT>
