<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; POLICE SEEK SUSPECT IN BANK ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard police are looking for a man who robbed a bank Thursday morning and 
fled on foot with an undisclosed amount of cash. 
</P>
<P>
 The man entered California Federal Bank at 2900 Saviers Road at about 11:15 
a.m., approached a teller and asked for money, telling her to "keep her hands 
up," according to Oxnard Police Sgt. Fred Berry. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber was described as a dark-haired Latino male, about 25 years old, 5 
foot, 9 inches tall, and 160 pounds. He was wearing a white and blue baseball 
cap, dark sunglasses and a white T-shirt with a dark blue logo.  
</P>
<P>
 The teller, who told police she did not see a gun or other weapon, turned over 
an undisclosed amount of money to the man, who leafed through the cash and 
fled. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Berry, the man was last seen running toward the area of Samuel 
Avenue and Lark Street. An investigation is continuing. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
