<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; POLICE DEPARTMENT TO BE HOST OF CAR SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hundreds of antique cars and street rods will be on display Sunday outside the 
Vintage Museum of Transportation and Wildlife when the Oxnard Police Department 
is host of the fifth annual Cops & Cruisers Car Show. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is a fund-raiser for various youth organizations, including Casa 
Pacifica, a Camarillo shelter for abused children. 
</P>
<P>
 "This show has really grown over the past five years," said Jan Paxton, who 
organized the event with her husband, Paul, in conjunction with the Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've got entries from as far south as San Diego and as far north as Paso 
Robles," Paxton said. "I've even got one from as far east as Tennessee." 
</P>
<P>
 There will be food booths, entertainment, three bands and vendors selling 
parts and equipment for classic car collectors and builders. This year, police 
volunteers have set up a boxing ring for demonstrations in boxing and martial 
arts. 
</P>
<P>
 The department's Special Weapons and Tactics squad also will hold a 
demonstration. At 3 p.m., awards will given out to more than 90 vehicles in 28 
categories, including best sports cars, street rods and nostalgic automobiles. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission to the outdoor display is free after 10 a.m. But entry into the 
vintage museum, located at 1421 Emerson Ave. in Oxnard, is $10. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
