<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ANGELES NATIONAL 
FOREST; FALL BLAMED IN DEATH OF COLLEGE BASEBALL STAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A college baseball star who was killed last weekend while hiking in the 
Angeles National Forest had lost his footing while taking a shortcut, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Upper Iowa University baseball standout Rick Perez, 20, fell about 75 feet, 
officials said.He was from El Monte. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 2:30 p.m. Saturday. Perez was flown to a Pasadena 
hospital, where he died later in the day. 
</P>
<P>
 A junior, Perez led Upper Iowa with a .401 batting average and had a school 
record 57 hits this season. The American Baseball Coaches Assn. named him to 
the All-Central Region second team as an outfielder. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm in shock. I'm sad. He was a really good kid," Upper Iowa Coach Rick 
Heller said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
