<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; DEFINING MOMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLIAM TUOHY, Times London Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Financial Times reader came up with the observation that there are four main 
types of football-oriented games: 
</P>
<P>
 British Assn. football: a game for gentlemen played by hooligans. 
</P>
<P>
 Rugby Union football: a game for hooligans played by gentlemen. 
</P>
<P>
 Rugby League football: a game for hooligans played by hooligans. 
</P>
<P>
 American football: a game for Americans played by Americans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
