<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEFORE DECIDING WHETHER TO MOVE UP, GONZALEZ FACES DIAZ TONIGHT AT FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In his first bout since defeating Michael Carbajal last February for 
two-thirds of the major light-flyweight titles, Humberto (Chiquita) Gonzalez is 
scheduled to fight Armando Diaz in a 10-round nontitle fight tonight at the 
Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez, 38-2 with 26 knockouts, is about to decide whether to pursue a third 
fight against Carbajal or move up to take a shot at one of the flyweight 
titles.He fought and defeated Diaz (22-16, eight KOs) last November. 
</P>
<P>
 In the previous Diaz fight, Gonzalez threw more than 1,000 punches in 10 
rounds, according to computer statistics. 
</P>
<P>
 That was Gonzalez's last tuneup before the Carbajal rematch at the Forum, in 
which Gonzalez won a decision and the International Boxing Federation and World 
Boxing Council championships and avenged his knockout loss to Carbajal in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 In a 10-round bout scheduled to precede the main event, undefeated 
junior-middleweight Alfred Ankamah (10-0, 10 KOs) will fight Luis Vasquez 
(29-6, 25 KOs). TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</TEXT>
