<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: BOOTH WINS JUNIOR GOLF IN NEVADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kellee Booth of Coto de Caza shot a final-round 70 to win the girls' division 
of the Las Vegas Founders' Legacy Junior Golf tournament Thursday in Henderson, 
Nev. 
</P>
<P>
 Booth finished with a three-day total of 212 on the 5,763-yard, par-72 Legacy 
Golf Club course.Booth, who will attend Arizona State in the fall, shot 67 in 
the opening round and 75 Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Lee of Fullerton shot 70 Thursday to finished second at 215. 
</P>
<P>
 Darren Angel of Northridge won the boys' division with a three-round total of 
211. John Lee of Placentia was the top Orange County finisher at 221. Jeffrey 
McGraw of Fullerton was at 223, Terry Noe of Fullerton 224 and Ben Garner of 
Lake Forest 225. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton pitcher Ted Silva has been chosen for the U.S. amateur 
baseball all-star team that will play in the World Championships next month. 
</P>
<P>
 Silva is one of 10 pitchers chosen for squad that will play 25 games, most of 
them against other national teams, before the World Championships from Aug. 
3-17 in Managua, Nicaragua. Silva had 13 saves as the closer for the Fullerton 
team that won the NCAA Midwest I Regional and advanced to the College World 
Series. The U.S. team trains in Millington, Tenn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
