<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUCKS OPEN ON THE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mighty Ducks will open their second NHL season with a three-game trip to 
Dallas, Edmonton and Vancouver, the team announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ducks open the season Oct. 1 at Dallas and follow with games at Edmonton 
(Oct. 5) and Vancouver (Oct. 7). Their first home game will be Oct. 9 against 
Calgary at The Pond of Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ducks also will play two games at neutral sites -- a Feb. 9 road game 
against St. Louis at the MGM Grand Arena in Las Vegas, and a March 11 home game 
against Dallas at San Antonio's Alamodome. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ducks' 1994-95 schedule (home games in CAPS; times to be announced): 
</P>
