<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCREENPLAY SEMINAR SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rancho Santiago Community College District will offer a seminar on how to 
write and sell screenplays on July 16. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-hour seminar will begin at 9 a.m. and focus on how to get the 
attention of readers, agents and producers as well as how to write a script 
people will want to buy. The cost of the seminar is $38, payable at the door, 
said district spokesman Dale Ruhe. 
</P>
<P>
 The class will be in Room R-115 of the Rancho Santiago campus, at 17th and 
Bristol streets. Call (714) 564-6220 for details. 
</P>
</TEXT>
