<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; MEDIA CITY MALL BANS INDOOR SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Media City Center mall in Burbank banned all indoor smoking this week, the 
last major shopping center in the San Fernando Valley to impose such a 
restriction. 
</P>
<P>
 Lighting up has been prohibited at the Fallbrook Mall, Northridge Fashion 
Center, Sherman Oaks Galleria, the Promenade at Woodland Hills, Topanga Plaza 
and, more recently, at the Glendale Galleria and Sherman Oaks Fashion Square. 
</P>
<P>
 The ban at the Burbank mall took effect Tuesday and restricts smoking to 
outdoor patio areas. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have been thinking about it for about six months," said Donna Lum, a 
spokeswoman for the Media City Center. "It just seemed like the time was right 
to do it." VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
