<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; PUBLIC INVITED TO REHAB GRADUATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People hoping to help someone who suffers from drug or alcohol dependency are 
invited to a graduation and picnic Sunday for students of a Van Nuys recovery 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, hosted by the Inter-Agency Drug Abuse Recovery Programs, will allow 
the public to ask questions about recovery from chemical dependency. 
</P>
<P>
 "Everybody knows somebody who is chemically addicted," said Kathie Mathis, the 
organization's program director. "One addict affects a minimum of 50 other 
people." 
</P>
<P>
 A barbecue, softball game and live band will entertain throughout the event, 
which runs from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. at Reseda Park, at the corner of Victory and 
Reseda boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit agency will graduate 17 clients at 11 a.m. Mathis said the 
agency, which has offices in Van Nuys and Newhall, treats about 200 clients 
annually. 
</P>
<P>
 "Not only do we provide services for the addict, we provide services for the 
family members, friends and loved ones," Mathis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cost for the four- to seven-month outpatient treatment program is done on a 
sliding scale, Mathis said. Chemically dependent clients can receive clinical 
assessment, counseling, drug testing and other services from the agency. 
</P>
<P>
 A donation of $5 per person for the picnic is requested. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
