<P>
 Spectrum, Caserta Part Company: Spectrum Information Technologies Inc. said it 
has ended its contract with Peter Caserta, the company's president who had been 
on leave since five associates were arrested last spring.The company also named 
four new directors, completing a restructuring of its board. Spectrum, holder 
of patents for wireless data transmission, gained attention for hiring former 
Apple Computer chief John Sculley as its CEO and chairman last fall. But 
Sculley left in February, and Spectrum is still searching for a new chief 
executive, said Edward Maskaly, who is filling the role temporarily. 
</P>
