it will end the 1984 agreement that settled a European Commission investigation 
of the company's alleged anti-competitive practices. IBM had agreed with the 
commission to supply information to rivals on product attachments, computer 
memory and software. But the computer maker said those commitments are no 
longer necessary in an age of "open" computer systems. 
</P>
