<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; ZISKIND TO FOX? PRODUCER ISN'T SAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Producer Laura Ziskind is the latest executive rumored to be headed to 20th 
Century Fox, to run a new mature-films wing. Ziskind, who just wrapped "To Die 
For" and has another 1 1/2 years to go on her production deal at TriStar 
Pictures, said she is surprised by the talk. 
</P>
<P>
 The purpose of the division, sources say, is to make adult-relationship movies 
that appeal to women. Fox already has a family film division and is in the 
midst of putting together a unit that will concentrate on art movies. 
</P>
<P>
 But Fox executives call the labels silly and say the purpose of the new 
divisions is to churn out even more films. The studio's long-range goal is to 
bulk up the production load to 40 movies a year. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tim Bennett has been named president of HARPO Productions, the Chicago-based 
production company for TV talk show host and producer Oprah Winfrey. Bennett 
was president and general manager of the Capital Cities/ABC-owned station WTVD 
in Raleigh-Durham, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
 * Noted entertainment analyst Lisbeth R. Barron is moving to SBCI Swiss Bank 
Corp. Investment Banking Inc. to head a new media investment banking operation. 
</P>
<P>
 Barron was senior media and entertainment industry analyst for nearly five 
years at S.G. Warburg & Co. Barron also provided The Times with weekly box 
office figures. 
</P>
<P>
 * Salah Hassanein, former president of Warner Bros. International Theaters, 
has been named president and chief operating officer of Todd-AO Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 * Marcelle Garfield has been named director of project management for Culver 
City-based Showscan Corp. Separately, Michael B. Ellis was named vice president 
of engineering and product development as well as chief technologist. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jim Yeager has been named head of publicity and public relations for WB, the 
new network formed by Warner Bros. and broadcast executive Jamie Kellner. 
Yeager was director of public relations for Universal Studios Hollywood. 
</P>
